rpl
------------------------------------------
rpl is a UN*X text replacement utility. It will replace strings with new
strings in multiple text files. It can work recursively over directories and
supports limiting the search to specific file suffixes.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.35-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-1
  cygport-0.18.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://www.laffeycomputer.com/rpl.html

Canonical download:
  http://downloads.laffeycomputer.com/current_builds/rpl-1.4.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack rpl-1.4.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./rpl-1.4.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/rpl-1.4.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/rpl-1.4.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(rpl)
  /usr/bin/rpl.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/rpl.README
  /usr/share/doc/rpl/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/rpl/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/rpl/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/man/man1/rpl.1.gz

